    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Currently Zend_Gdata_Extension_ExtendedProperty implements data storage by using key and value attributes. This appears to be consistent with Google's previous documentation</p>

<p>However, Google's new Contacts Data API docs seem to be changing things.</p>

<p>bq.  Value of the extended property may be stored as a value (arbitrary string) <em>or</em> an XML blob (these are mutually exclusive; instead of a valid XML blob plain text can be used).
<a href="http://code.google.com/apis/contacts/reference.html#gd:extendedProperty">http://code.google.com/apis/contacts/â€¦</a></p>

